# 🐳 Docker — Quick Revision Cheat Sheet

---

## What is Docker?
Package your app + dependencies + runtime into a **Container** that runs anywhere.
> Build → Ship → Run

---

## VM vs Container (Quick)

| | Virtual Machine | Container |
|---|---|---|
| OS | Full Guest OS per VM | Shares Host OS kernel |
| Size | GBs | MBs |
| Startup | Minutes | Seconds |
| Isolation | Hardware-level | Process-level |
| Resource | Heavy | Lightweight |

---

## Stack (Bottom → Top)

| VM Stack | Container Stack |
|---|---|
| Hardware | Physical Server |
| Host OS | Host OS |
| Hypervisor | Container Engine (Docker) |
| Guest OS | ~~No Guest OS~~ ✅ |
| Libraries/Binaries | Libraries/Binaries |
| App | App |

---

## Docker Flow

```
Dockerfile → build → Image → push → Registry
                                        ↓ pull
                               Dev / Test / Prod
                                     ↓ run
                                  Container
```

---

## Architecture (3 components)

| Component | Role |
|---|---|
| **Docker Client** | Where you type commands |
| **Docker Daemon (dockerd)** | Does the actual work |
| **Registry** | Stores images (Docker Hub, Quay.io, JFrog) |

### Command internals (one line each)
- `docker build` → Client → Daemon → reads Dockerfile → creates Image locally
- `docker push` → Client → Daemon → uploads Image to Registry
- `docker pull` → Client → Daemon → downloads Image from Registry
- `docker run` → Client → Daemon → Container Runtime → Container starts

---

## Why Containers over VMs?
- No Guest OS overhead = faster + lighter
- Starts in seconds not minutes
- Same image runs on Dev/Test/Prod — no environment mismatch
- Run many containers where only few VMs would fit

---

## Key Terms

| Term | One line |
|---|---|
| Dockerfile | Recipe to build an image |
| Image | Read-only blueprint (built from Dockerfile) |
| Container | Running instance of an image |
| Registry | Remote storage for images |
| Docker Daemon | Background engine that manages everything |
| Container Runtime | Actually starts/stops containers (e.g. containerd) |

